  "prompt": "How do bottle caps work in Pokemon Sun / Moon?",
  "response": "In Pok\u00e9mon Sun and Moon, bottle caps are used for Hyper Training, a feature that allows you to maximize a Pok\u00e9mon's Individual Values (IVs) at the Hau'oli City Mall. Here's how it works:\n\n1. You need to have a Pok\u00e9mon at level 100 to use Hyper Training.\n\n2. Go to the Stat Judge in the Hau'oli City Mall (located in the first shopping district).\n\n3. You can use one bottle cap to maximize a single stat's IV to its maximum potential.\n\n4. A Gold Bottle Cap can be used to max out all six of a Pok\u00e9mon's stats at once.\n\n5. Bottle caps can be obtained through various methods:\n- Some are found as items in the game\n- Can be won from certain in-game activities\n- Purchased from the Battle Royal Dome\n- Received as rewards\n\n6. Hyper Training does not change the Pok\u00e9mon's actual base stats, but it effectively allows max IVs for competitive battling.\n\nThis feature is particularly useful for training Pok\u00e9mon caught later in the game or received through trades, which might not have perfect IVs from birth.",
